abstract: Free-market capitalism won’t survive unless it makes structural changes toward long-term investing.
snippet: Free-market capitalism won’t survive unless it makes structural changes toward long-term investing.
lead_paragraph: In 2007, James Rogers did the unthinkable. As chief executive of Duke Energy, one of the largest coal-powered utilities in the country, he lobbied for the passage of aggressive cap-and-trade legislation. The bill, if passed, would have imposed billions of dollars in costs on his business, and it was vigorously opposed by the coal industry’s primary lobbyist.

abstract: Philip Yancey, an evangelical Christian writer, responds to my questions, and my doubts.
snippet: Philip Yancey, an evangelical Christian writer, responds to my questions, and my doubts.
lead_paragraph: Welcome to the latest in my occasional series of conversations about Christianity. Here’s my interview, edited for space, with Philip Yancey, an evangelical Christian writer who has more than 15 million books in print in more than 50 languages.

abstract: Isaiah Livers went up for a dunk and missed, drawing a foul in the process. Then he walked around looking gimpy and holding his left leg.
snippet: Isaiah Livers went up for a dunk and missed, drawing a foul in the process. Then he walked around looking gimpy and holding his left leg.
lead_paragraph: ANN ARBOR, Mich. — Isaiah Livers went up for a dunk and missed, drawing a foul in the process. Then he walked around looking gimpy and holding his left leg.
headline_main: Livers Hurt, but No. 14 Michigan Beats Presbyterian 86-44
headline_print_headline: Livers Hurt, but No. 14 Michigan Beats Presbyterian 86-44

abstract: Yoenis Céspedes' base salary next year was cut to $6 million from its original $29.5 million as part of an amended contract with the New York Mets that avoided a grievance hearing, according to details obtained by The Associated Press.
snippet: Yoenis Céspedes' base salary next year was cut to $6 million from its original $29.5 million as part of an amended contract with the New York Mets that avoided a grievance hearing, according to details obtained by The Associated Press.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — Yoenis Céspedes' base salary next year was cut to $6 million from its original $29.5 million as part of an amended contract with the New York Mets that avoided a grievance hearing, according to details obtained by The Associated Press.
headline_main: AP Exclusive: Céspedes Base Pay Cut From $29.5M to $6M
headline_print_headline: AP Exclusive: Céspedes Base Pay Cut From $29.5M to $6M

abstract: Romelu Lukaku scored twice to lead Inter Milan to a comfortable 4-0 win over lowly Genoa on Saturday as they rejoined Juventus at the top of Serie A on Saturday.
snippet: Romelu Lukaku scored twice to lead Inter Milan to a comfortable 4-0 win over lowly Genoa on Saturday as they rejoined Juventus at the top of Serie A on Saturday.
lead_paragraph: MILAN — Romelu Lukaku scored twice to lead Inter Milan to a comfortable 4-0 win over lowly Genoa on Saturday as they rejoined Juventus at the top of Serie A on Saturday.
headline_main: Lukaku Notches Brace as Inter Rejoin Juve at Top
headline_print_headline: Lukaku Notches Brace as Inter Rejoin Juve at Top

abstract: We’ve lost our ability to take comfort in small things.
snippet: We’ve lost our ability to take comfort in small things.
lead_paragraph: Recently I have been forced to think a bit about happiness. It’s not something I’ve done before. I have been too busy living. But when an interview with me appeared in The Sunday Times under the headline “Why ‘This Is Happiness’ Author Niall Williams Is Happily Out of Step,” I began to realize that it was not just me but the idea of happiness itself that was out of step with the times, and that it required some mental adjusting, not to say daring, to say aloud the title of my novel.
